			<title>GCB Voted Bank Of The Year</title>
			<link>http://www.gcb.com.gh/news/156-gcb-voted-bank-of-the-year</link>
			<guid isPermaLink="true">http://www.gcb.com.gh/news/156-gcb-voted-bank-of-the-year</guid>
			<description><![CDATA[<div class="feed-description"><p><img class="caption" title="GCB awarded CIMG bank of the year 2012" src="http://www.gcb.com.gh/images/news/2013/gcb_cimg_bank_of_the_year.jpg" alt="GCB awarded CIMG bank of the year 2012" align="left" />Ghana Commercial Bank Limited (GCB) has been adjudged the Bank of the Year, 2012, by the Chartered Institute of Marketing Ghana (CIMG).</p>
<p>The award is in recognition of expert financial solutions and e-banking products the Bank has introduced over the past two years which have helped to improve service to customers and which have made GCB notable among giants in the banking industry.</p>
<p>The award coincides with the celebration of 60 years of banking excellence in Ghana by GCB this year.<br />Mr. Samuel Sarpong, the Chief Transformation Officer of the Bank who received the award on behalf of the Bank said the award is a reflection of the major strides achieved under the transformation exercise the Bank embarked on two years ago.</p>
<p>Since then the automation of the Bank's services and the introduction of a range of e-banking products namely SMS banking, Smartpay, 24-hour Personal Loan, MasterCard and most recently GCB e-alerts and e-statements have positioned GCB positively in the mind of customers.</p>
<p>The transformation has touched GCB's products and services, processes, staff and systems with the key objective of re-positioning GCB as the leading financial institution in Ghana.</p>
<p>Mr. Sarpong explained that GCB's innovations in the banking sector, support to communities and overall performance as well as having made such giant strides in product introduction and performance over the past few years and this past year in particular have been noticed by industry watchers</p>
<p>He said while the transformation is on-going to ensure that GCB evolves into a world-class institution, the staff are striving to build a reputation for the Bank as one that can be trusted to deliver superior returns to its shareholders and trusted by its customers to deliver excellent service.</p>
<p>He gave the assurance that the Bank would continue to respond to changes in the industry not only to remain in business but also to excel at what it does to satisfy the various stakeholders adding that "this resilience has culminated in making us the Bank of the Year today."<br />He dedicated the award to the Bank's investors, customers and Ghanaians from whom GCB has derived the strength to challenge itself to perform better at each stage.</p>
